---
import IndexPage from "../../layouts/IndexPage.astro";
import { AxeThrowingBusinessCalculator } from "../../components/calculators/axe-throwing/AxeThrowingBusinessCalculator";
import { Calculator } from 'lucide-react';
import YouTubeEmbed from '../../components/YouTubeEmbed.astro';
import ImageEmbed from '../../components/ImageEmbed.astro';
import AuthorBox from '../../components/AuthorBox.astro';

export const frontmatter = {
  comment: false,
  donate: false,
  title: "Axe Throwing Business Calculator: Revenue & Profit Projections",
  description: "Plan your axe throwing business with our comprehensive financial calculator. Get detailed revenue projections, startup costs, and profitability analysis.",
  author: "Brett Lindenberg",
  category: "Business Calculators",
  date: "2025-01-6",
  tags: [""],
  image: {
    url: "",
    alt: ""
  }
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
  "name": frontmatter.title,
  "description": frontmatter.description,
  "applicationCategory": "BusinessApplication",
  "operatingSystem": "Web Browser",
  "offers": {
    "@type": "Offer",
    "price": "0",
    "priceCurrency": "USD"
  },
  "featureList": [
    "Axe throwing business revenue calculator",
    "Startup cost analysis",
    "Lane utilization tracking",
    "Profit margin calculation",
    "Break-even analysis",
    "Financial reporting"
  ]
};
---

<IndexPage 
  title={frontmatter.title}
  description={frontmatter.description}
  author={frontmatter.author}
  date={frontmatter.date}
  comment={frontmatter.comment}
  donate={frontmatter.donate}
  image={frontmatter.image}
  category={frontmatter.category}
  tags={frontmatter.tags}>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
  
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-skin-fill py-8 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-base text-skin-base">
          Thinking about starting an axe throwing business? This calculator cuts through the guesswork giving you everything from startup costs to monthly profits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <AxeThrowingBusinessCalculator client:load />
    </div>
  </div>
     
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mt-12 text-skin-base">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use This Calculator</h2>
    <p>Start by entering these key details:</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6">1. Business Information</h3>
    <p>Enter your business name in the designated field. While "Abe's Axe to Grind" serves as the default name, you can customize this to match your brand identity.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6">2. Facility Setup & Initial Investment</h3>
    <p>Your startup costs include several key components:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Leasehold Improvements:</strong> Default $200,000 - covers essential renovations, build-out costs, safety features, seating, tables, and decor</li>
      <li><strong>Lane Configuration:</strong> Default $7,500 per lane for standard setup (source: <a href="https://axcitement.com/2020/09/27/what-does-it-cost-to-build-an-axe-throwing-business/">Axcitement.com</a>)</li>
      <li>Standard layout: 8 lanes (6 feet width, 24 feet depth per lane)</li>
      <li>Equipment Investment: $150 per axe by default</li>
    </ul>

    <ImageEmbed
      src="/images/mobile-axe-throwing.png"
      alt="mobile axe throwing"
      description="Add a mobile axe throwing trailer to further increase revenue with this business model."
    />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8">3. Revenue Calculations</h3>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Peak Hours (Friday-Sunday):</p>
        <pre class="bg-skin-card p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
Peak Revenue = (Hourly Rate × Number of Lanes × Peak Utilization × Peak Hours × 4.3 weeks) × Average Group Size</pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Off-Peak Hours:</p>
        <pre class="bg-skin-card p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
Off-Peak Revenue = (Hourly Rate × Number of Lanes × Off-Peak Utilization × Off-Peak Hours × 4.3 weeks) × Average Group Size</pre>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="font-bold mb-2">Corporate Events:</p>
        <pre class="bg-skin-card p-4 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
Corporate Revenue = Event Price × Number of Monthly Events</pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <ImageEmbed
      src="/images/golden-axe-throwing-and-bar.png"
      alt="axe throwing bar"
      description="Inside Golden Axe Throwing and Bar in SLC."
    />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8">4. Monthly Operating Costs</h3>
    <p>Default monthly costs based on industry averages:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Rent:</strong> $5,000 default monthly rate</li>
      <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> $500 monthly ($5,000-$7,500 annually per <a href="https://axcitement.com/2022/02/06/how-much-is-axe-throwing-insurance/">Axcitement Insurance Guide</a>)</li>
      <li><strong>Utilities:</strong> $800 default monthly rate</li>
      <li><strong>Staff wages:</strong> $5,000 default monthly rate</li>
      <li><strong>Marketing:</strong> $2,000 default monthly allocation</li>
      <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> $100 per lane monthly default</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Understanding The Results</h2>
    <p>
      The calculator provides a comprehensive breakdown of your investment and potential returns:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>Total initial investment required</li>
      <li>Revenue streams breakdown (peak hours, off-peak, corporate events)</li>
      <li>Monthly profit projections</li>
      <li>Break-even timeline</li>
      <li>5-year growth projections (conservative and optimistic scenarios)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Industry Research & Case Studies</h2>
    <p>
      My research draws heavily from industry leaders like Axcitement.com, which provides comprehensive data on startup costs and operations. A standout case study comes from <a href="https://www.forgedaxe.ca/">Forged Axe Throwing</a> in Whistler and Victoria, British Columbia, which generates $60,000 in monthly revenue.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6">Marketing Strategies from Successful Venues</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Grand Opening Strategy:</strong> Forged Axe Throwing's successful launch included strategic banner placement near breweries, distributing 500 flyers to local businesses, and targeted social media advertising.</li>
      <li><strong>Traditional Marketing:</strong> Tourist rack brochures and local newspaper ads proved surprisingly effective.</li>
      <li><strong>Mobile Extensions:</strong> Adding a mobile axe throwing trailer created additional revenue streams and marketing opportunities.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-Channel Approach:</strong> Combining digital marketing with traditional methods for maximum reach.</li>
    </ul>

    <YouTubeEmbed 
      id="T80F1-3NWFU"
      title="How to Start a $60K per Month Axe Throwing Business"
      className="mb-8"
    />

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-12 mb-4">Related Tools:</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>
        <a href="/business-calculators/hole-in-one-challenge-revenue-and-prize-calculator/">Hole-in-One Challenge Revenue and Prize Calculator</a>
      </strong>: Much like an axe-throwing venue, a Hole-in-One Challenge requires building awareness, generating excitement, and a marketing machine to get regular paying customers. Both ideas lean heavily on the experience factor: offering something fun, memorable, and a little outside the box.
    </p>

    <main>
      <article>
        <slot />
      </article>
      <AuthorBox />
    </main>
  </div>
</IndexPage>